us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FrameVector4DReadOnly

  • All Superinterfaces:
    FrameTuple4DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Vector4DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedFrameVector4DBasics, FrameVector4DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameVector4D

    public interface FrameVector4DReadOnly
extends us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Vector4DReadOnly, FrameTuple4DReadOnly
    Read-only interface for a 4D vector expressed in a given reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Vector4DReadOnly, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FrameVector4DReadOnly. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on vectors occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FrameVector4DReadOnly extends Vector4DReadOnly, it is compatible with methods only requiring Vector4DReadOnly. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FrameVector4DReadOnly.

    • Method Detail

      • geometricallyEquals

        default boolean geometricallyEquals(FrameVector4DReadOnly other,
                                    double epsilon)
        Compares this to other to determine if the two frame vectors are geometrically similar, i.e. the length of the distance between them is less than or equal to epsilon.
        Parameters:
        other - the frame vector to compare to. Not modified.
        epsilon - the tolerance of the comparison.
        Returns:
        true if the two frame vectors represent the same geometry, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if other is not expressed in the same reference frame as this.
